<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>4webm</title>
    <link rel="shortcut icon" type="image/x-icon" href="{{favicon}}"/>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="{{global_style}}" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="{{style}}" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="boardBanner">
      <div id="bannerCnt" class="title desktop">
        <img alt="4chan" src="/banner.png" />
      </div>
      <div class="boardTitle">4webm</div>
      <div class="boardSubtitle">
        Load and play all webms in a 4chan thread (highly recommend /wsg/ threads)<br />
        4webm, nor its creator, are associated with 4chan.org<br />
        Please consider giving me a <a href="https://github.com/ScottyFillups/4chan-webm-player">star</a> :)<br />
        Want something added? Feel free to leave a feature request <a href="https://github.com/scootykins/4webm/issues">here!</a> Love ya &lt;3
      </div>
    </div>
    <hr class="abovePostForm" />
    <div id="togglePostFormLink" class="desktop">
      [<a id="gen-playlist" href="#">Generate a New Playlist</a>]
      [<a id="play-local-files" href="#">Play Local Files</a>]
      <input type="file" id="local-files-input" multiple style="display: none;" />
    </div>
    <form id="thread-form" class="hide" action="">
      <input id="thread-url" size="45" placeholder="Enter a 4chan thread URL" />
      <button id="submit-url">Load webms!</button>
    </form>
    <hr />
    <div class="globalMessage">
      <h3>**Update** I'm building a site called <a href="https://tutturu.tv">tutturu.tv</a> that lets you watch anything with friends together; you should check it out! :)</h3>
    </div>
    <div style="text-align: center">
      <p style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">
        You can also load a thread by replacing '4chan' with '4webm' in a thread URL and visiting it,
      </p>
      <p style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">
        Keyboard shortcuts: Left/right -&gt; prev/next, up/down -&gt; volume, spacebar -&gt; pause/play, l -&gt; loop, f -&gt; fullscreen
      </p>
    </div>
    <hr />
    <div class='body-cnt'>
      <div class="player-cnt">
        <div id="menu">
          <div class="fileText">
            <a id="filename" href=""></a>
          </div>
          <div id="menu-misc">
            [<a id="fullscreen" class="hide" href="#">Fullscreen</a>]
          </div>
          <label>
            [<input id="loop" type="checkBox">Loop]
          </label>
          [<a id="prev" href="#">Prev</a>]
          [<a id="next" href="#">Next</a>]
          [<a id="show-goto" href="#">Goto</a>]
          <form id="goto" class="hide">
            <input id="goto-input" type=text" size="4">
            <input type="submit" value="Play">
          </form>
          <span id="status"></span>
        </div>
        <video id="player" width="650" height="400" controls>
          Your browser does not support the video tag! ;-;
        </video>
      </div>
      <div id="playlist"></div>
      <hr>
      <div class="footerLinks">
        [<a id="return" href="#">Return</a>]
        [<a id="update" href="#">Update</a>]
      </div>
      <hr>
    </div>
    <script src="/bundle.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
